Question: If a walker has cleanup logic that must run even when the walker might disengage partway through a traversal, why is putting that logic in an exit ability unreliable, and what is the recommended alternative?

Ground-truth passage:
```jac
# Before: Exit ability would run before disengage stops traversal
walker MyWalker {
    can process with MyNode entry {
        if some_condition { disengage; }
        visit [-->];
    }
    can cleanup with Root exit {
        # This WOULD run before disengage in old semantics
        print("Cleanup");
    }
}

